summary: This document is an AT&T wireline call detail record, produced on June 17, 2020, covering the period from March 1 to June 15, 2020. It logs numerous calls between several phone numbers, likely as part of an investigation into communications related to the Epstein case.

events.title: Telephone Communications Logged
events.description: AT&T call detail records were queried and produced, logging numerous calls between specific phone numbers over a three-and-a-half month period.

keyFacts: The document is a confidential AT&T wireline call detail record produced for an investigation.
It logs calls from March 1, 2020, to June 15, 2020, with timestamps, originating/terminating numbers, and call durations.
The records were stored and provided in OTC (likely a reference to a time zone or storage format).
The document is marked as proprietary and confidential, for use by authorized persons only.
The call log shows frequent communication between several phone numbers, including numbers 829, 343, 827, 314, and 9.
